In times of need 2 or 3 soldiers would man the crossbow. One to aim the
device and another 1 or 2 ready to reload it as soon as a bolt is fired.
Although they take many times longer to load and fire the a longbow the
range of the device is a 100 yards further, able to reach beyond the
front lines of an incatious enemy.
~
